                            <comment id="14098705" author="tgraves" created="Fri, 15 Aug 2014 16:08:19 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that in yarn-cluster mode the client side does quit, but the application master is still running on the cluster.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="14101134" author="tgraves" created="Mon, 18 Aug 2014 19:24:33 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Note that this also isn&apos;t an issue on hadoop 0.23 because there it shoots the containers after unregister.  In hadoop 2.x it doesn&apos;t shoot them as aggressively to give the application time to cleanup .&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
